<section id="site.settings">
    <title>General Settings</title>

    <para>
        As an administrator, additional option appears for you in the <guibutton>Manage</guibutton>
        menu:

        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/screen-toolbar_menu-general_settings.png"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </para>

    <para>
        When you click <guimenuitem>General Settings</guimenuitem>, the
        <emphasis role="screen">General Settings</emphasis> is displayed.

        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/screen-general_settings.png"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </para>

    <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Title</term>

            <listitem>
                The title of your site.
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
            <term>Description</term>

            <listitem>
                A description of your site. This is included in meta tags on each page.
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry id="robots">
            <term>robots.txt</term>

            <listitem>
                A "Robots Exclusion Standard" definition, to instruct search engine robots which
                portions of your site <emphasis>not</emphasis> to index. For further details, please
                see <ulink url="http://www.robotstxt.org/orig.html">A Standard for Robot
                Exclusion</ulink> at
                <ulink url="http://www.robotstxt.org/">www.robotstxt.org</ulink>, and
                <ulink url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robots_exclusion_standard">Robots Exclusion
                Standard</ulink> at <ulink url="http://www.wikipedia.org/">Wikipedia</ulink>.
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para>
        The Perforce Server connection settings are also presented to assist with any administrative
        tasks you may need to perform outside of &product.name;.
    </para>
</section>
